@node Requirements "I need all this?"
@font "Helvetica.font" 13

 @{b}@{u}That is what you need to use all these pretty brilliant looking icons :)@{uu}@{ub}

   - an Amiga - mhm...
   - Workbench 3.5 or 3.9 (Kickstart 3.1 ROMs)
   - icon.library (V44.x)
   - DIROpus Magelan (for NewIcons the V5.82 patch is required!)
   - or other startmenu-tool like screentab
   - an average hight screen resolution >=800x600(square)
     icons might be used on vga-resolutions (640x480) used as standard icons, not just for
     startmenus or toolbars!?
   - pretty much colors(AGA with 256colors, better use a gfx-card in 16/24bit!)
   - some time to exchange or insert the icons :)


@endnode

@node Tools "Used hardware and tools"
@font "Helvetica.font" 13

 @{b}@{u}The following hardware has been used to create these icons:@{uu}@{ub}

   - Amiga 1200T and Blizzard 1260/SCSI-Kit with 96MB Fast
   - equipped with Prelude (+MPGit), X-Surf ethernet, Hypercom3+, ISDN SpeedViper
   - Cybervision 64/3D and Sony 210ES 17" Monitor
   - Alpha data 400dpi mouse for precise handling and much more
   - AmigaAMP and tons of MPGs for motivation at nights
   - pretty much coffee B)

   - TV Paint
   - AdPro
   - IconEdit from OS3.5/OS3.9 package
   - Cybergrab

@endnode

@node projekte "Some other projects..."
@font "Helvetica.font" 13

 @{b}@{u}Other AMIGA projecs and websites you might like to visit...@{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}http://www.synotec-newmedia.de@{ub}

 My business homepage. Also uses flash and javascript but is also fully enabled for Amiga browsers like
 Ibrowse or Aweb. Here you find latest desktop themes, graphics, icons and sounds. If you also own a
 PC have a look for free games.

 @{b}http://www.paulnolan.com@{ub}

 The homepage of Photogenics author Paul Nolan with some tutorials and more. Nice programme with still some
 bugs. Hopefully he will fix that soon..

 @{b}http://www.amiga-software.com@{ub}

 A collection of Amiga links. Wasting just some spare time on it..

 @{b}http://www.tamar.net@{ub}

 The homepage of (hopefully) forthcoming game

 @{b}http://www.eternity-computer.de@{ub}

 Amiga hard- and software near Cologne/Germany with a nice Amiga based online-shop.


 I also already supported the authors of other Amiga PRGs like EASys!, Digibooster, Pegase, Frogger...

 A lot more links to all the projects (gaming and internet) can be found on my business homepage (sorry, but it is
 German only)

@endnode

